Pre-Game Insights: Armenia will face Latvia at the Vazgen Sargsyan Republican Stadium on September 7th, 2024, in their opening UEFA Nations League match.
Armenia ended a four-game losing streak with a win against Kazakhstan, while Latvia last won on June 7th, 2024, against the Faroe Islands.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match is Armenia's first in League C of the Nations League, aiming to build on their recent win.
Latvia, ranked 137th by FIFA, will face Armenia, 40 places above them.
Others: The head-to-head record shows Armenia with one win, Latvia with two wins, and one draw.
The latest prediction favors Armenia to win 1-0, with betting tips including under 2.5 goals and both teams not scoring.
